<p>Vietnam’s environment ministry and media reports say days of torrential rain and landslides have killed at least 90 people and left 12 missing across central and south-central regions as of Sunday, November 23 [bbc.com#1][theguardian.com#1]. Flooding has inundated tourist areas and triggered landslides, with whole sections of Nha Trang flooded and deadly slides near Da Lat [thehindu.com#1]. The government estimates $343 million in economic losses across five provinces [aljazeera.com#1]. Rains have persisted since late October, compounding damage and hampering rescue efforts [theguardian.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/_38uIx7goFbo6GMRpel8_7cxkeTIKvnvO1unELpkhSUvQaLBQk86CKmr7HNONSztuX_7ZS5w3X24vXQmNokcqGjJMzTHi5vZgUbrW4QUZPKg6QlsMGrmt6Ma1vNeL41QSeuFZi7vUITitVYo5CvflvJeSccUG2OpX1dB3m6fIHedTVq9HaZJ' alt='Floodwaters and landslide debris in Vietnam’s central region after days of torrential rain.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Casualty figures: The death toll has reached 90, with 12 people still missing amid widespread flooding and landslides [bbc.com#1][theguardian.com#1][firstpost.com#1]</li><li>Hardest-hit province: Most of the fatalities occurred in the mountainous central province of Dak Lak, according to the environment ministry [theguardian.com#1]</li><li>Tourist hubs affected: Whole sections of coastal Nha Trang were inundated last week, while deadly landslides struck highland passes around Da Lat [thehindu.com#1]</li><li>Displacement and rescue: Relentless rains have displaced thousands, and rescue teams are searching for the missing [firstpost.com#1][theguardian.com#1]</li><li>Economic losses: The government estimates $343 million in damages across five provinces [aljazeera.com#1]</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Vietnam environment ministry: Reported the death toll rising to 90 with 12 people missing after days of heavy rain and landslides [theguardian.com#1] (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/nov/23/vietnam-flooding-deaths-landslides-rain-dak-lak'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Rescue services: Continuing search-and-rescue operations as thousands have been displaced across central and south-central Vietnam [firstpost.com#1] (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/relentless-rains-sweep-vietnam-leaving-90-dead-as-rescue-teams-search-for-survivors-13953194.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Local authorities in tourist regions: Reported inundation in Nha Trang and landslides near Da Lat, affecting travel routes and hillside passes [thehindu.com#1] (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/vietnam-flood-death-toll-rises/article70313613.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/23/death-toll-from-vietnam-floods-rises-to-90-several-still-missing'>Death toll from Vietnam floods rises to 90, several still missing</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/nov/23/vietnam-flooding-deaths-landslides-rain-dak-lak'>Vietnam flooding death toll reaches 90 amid landslides and relentless rain</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cwywl8g31g7o'>Vietnam floods leave at least 90 dead and 12 missing</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/relentless-rains-sweep-vietnam-leaving-90-dead-as-rescue-teams-search-for-survivors-13953194.html'>Relentless rains sweep Vietnam, leaving 90 dead as rescue teams search for survivors</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/vietnam-flood-death-toll-rises/article70313613.ece'>Vietnam flood death toll rises to 90</a> - thehindu.com</li></ul>